(32, 'New Release v0.92 - movable objects', 'new-release-v092-movable-objects', '', '<p style="text-align: justify;"><img style="float: right;" alt="box" src="images/stories/box.png" height="150" width="150" /></p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 12pt; color: #a7fafa;">The team is happy to introduce you to a new release featuring the movable objects.</span></p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 12pt; color: #a7fafa;">In addition the character animations and moving speed are now totally in sync...&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <br /></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;"> </span><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 12pt; color: #a7fafa;"> \r\n', '\r\n</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"> </p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"> </p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 12pt; color: #a7fafa;">Here is the complete list of new features:</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><br /><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 12pt; color: #a7fafa;">- some objects are now movable (boxes, statues)</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"> </p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 12pt; color: #a7fafa;">- a new quest has been added in citadel harbor (talk to the grobo close to the warehouse to see)</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"> </p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"> </p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 12pt; color: #a7fafa;">- the movable objects can take lifts or activate triggers on the floor. You can test it in the temple of Bü using the statue to activate the floor switch.<br /></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"> </p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 12pt; color: #a7fafa;">- the movable objects are replicated to other people''s computers via ghost objects.<br /></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><br /><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 12pt; color: #a7fafa;">- character animation and movement speed are now synchronized. Try the discrete or aggresive modes to see the difference. You can also notice it when going up ladders.</span><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 12pt; color: #a7fafa;">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><br /><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 12pt; color: #a7fafa;">- a crash reporter has been added to the game. In the case your game crashes a dialog will appear asking you to send a crash report to the MBN forum. If you wish for the game to become better and more stable please post them, this will help us a lot!</span><br /><br /><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 12pt; color: #a7fafa;">&nbsp;</span><br /><br /><span style="color: #a7fafa;"><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;">Hope you enjoy this release. Now we will be closing the poll and start working on the next choseen feature: fight with monsters. Thanks for giving your opinion, there will be other polls like this in the future so stay tuned ;)</span></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"> </p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="color: #a7fafa;"><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;"><br /></span></span></p>', 1, 2, 0, 1, '2010-08-18 20:02:15', 62, '', '2010-08-31 15:24:19', 62, 66, '2010-09-02 17:49:04', '2010-08-18 20:02:15', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', '', 