(31, 'Web chat', 'web-chat', '', '<p><img style="margin-left: 10px; float: right;" alt="chatimg" src="images/stories/chatimg.png" height="150" width="150" /></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"> </p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 12pt; color: #a7fafa;">Here is a small update of the website featuring the <a href="index.php?option=com_wrapper&view=wrapper&Itemid=29">web chat</a>.</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 12pt; color: #a7fafa;"><br /></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 12pt; color: #a7fafa;">Thanks to this new feature you can now chat with people playing the game directly </span><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 12pt; color: #a7fafa;">from the website!</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"> </p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"> </p>\r\n<p /><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 12pt; color: #a7fafa;" /> \r\n', '\r\n</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 12pt; color: #a7fafa;">This can be usefull for example if you can not connect to the game from where you are but still want to stay connected.</span></p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 12pt; color: #a7fafa;">You could also ask directly for support there if you have trouble starting the game.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 12pt; color: #a7fafa;"><br /></span></p>', 1, 2, 0, 1, '2010-08-01 19:26:44', 66, '', '2010-08-16 21:30:51', 66, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2010-08-01 19:22:10', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', '', '', 10, 0, 5, '', '', 0, 683, ''),
(33, 'New Release', 'new-release', '', 'New quest done! :lol: Moving objects works very well. But... I think that the time you have to wait for Twinsen takes it''s first step it''s too long, don''t you think? :-P\r\n\r\nCongratulations for your great work.', '', 1, 3, 0, 3, '2010-08-19 12:25:23', 546, 'Sara', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', '', '', 1, 32, 1, '', '', 0, 0, ''),
(34, 'nice release', 'nice-release', '', 'working well..\r\n\r\nsadly, i think a filter is needed to stop the language and stuff coming out of the little kiddies that seam to be floating around here these days...', '', 1, 3, 0, 3, '2010-08-24 15:47:44', 592, 'Manic Man', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', '', '', 1, 32, 1, '', '', 0, 0, ''),
(35, 'New world: Colozen', 'new-world-colozen', '', '<p style="text-align: justify;"><img style="float: right;" alt="Colozenimage" src="images/stories/Colozenimage.png" height="150" width="150" /></p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 12pt; color: #a7fafa;">A new world has been added to LBANet called Colozen.</span></p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 12pt; color: #a7fafa;">The world is made by DarkOnistar. You can visit it by selecting it on the top of the world list.             </span></p>\r\n<p /><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 12pt; color: #a7fafa;" /> \r\n', '\r\n</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"> </p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"> </p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"> </p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 12pt; color: #a7fafa;">Colozen is a new world with its own storyline going on.</span></p>\r\n<p><br /><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 12pt; color: #a7fafa;">You start off as a clone and learn more about the three factions: Colobees, Techlones and Magilonies.</span><br /><br /><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 12pt; color: #a7fafa;">To find out more visit the Colozen thread on ''Magicball Network''.</span></p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 12pt; color: #a7fafa;">---</span><br /><br /><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 12pt; color: #a7fafa;">World by: ''DarkOnistar''</span><br /><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 12pt; color: #a7fafa;">Special thanks to: ''Rincevent'' and ''Mazaka151''</span></p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="color: #a7fafa;"><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;"><br /></span></span></p>', 1, 2, 0, 1, '2010-09-02 17:48:58', 66, '', '2010-09-09 19:43:40', 66, 66, '2010-10-10 17:38:44', '2010-09-02 17:48:25', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', '', '', 7, 0, 3, '', '', 0, 677, ''),
(36, '.', '2010-09-02-21-11-25', '', 'Special thanks to Leoboe for fixing the image to have transparent corners.\r\n\r\nI look forward to all your ideas on the forum, also feel free to post any bugs that you feel are bothering you.', '', 1, 3, 0, 3, '2010-09-02 21:11:25', 759, 'DarkOnistar', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', '', '', 1, 35, 1, '', '', 0, 0, ''),
(37, 'Useful for when you crash', 'useful-for-when-you-crash', '', 'When your game crashes, normally we all try to log back in only to find that the server says "No! your already in!" so if you use webchat you can see when your other-self has left the game and you can rejoin again.\r\n\r\nAlso its useful to tell people why you suddenly left, as well as speaking to people ingame when you don''t want to go ingame yourself.', '', 1, 3, 0, 3, '2010-09-02 22:21:04', 759, 'DarkOnistar', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', '', '', 1, 31, 1, '', '', 0, 0, ''),
(38, 'Happy 1st', 'happy-1st', '', 'Your English isn''t that bad.\r\n\r\nI''m suprised this is a year old; this project really has come quite some way since it was first talked about.\r\n\r\nAlot of people talk about projects on the forums, then start a project and then drop it.  This project is still going strong and whats more its starting to become a favourite to the community.\r\n\r\n- Keep up the good work  8-)', '', 1, 3, 0, 3, '2010-09-02 22:24:16', 759, 'DarkOnistar', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', '', '', 1, 15, 1, '', '', 0, 0, ''),
(39, 'New game engine demo', 'new-game-engine-demo', '', '<p style="text-align: justify;"><img style="float: right;" alt="lba2map150" src="images/stories/lba2map150.png" height="150" width="150" /></p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 12pt; color: #a7fafa;">As promised here is a demo if the new game engine, featuring LBA2 outside maps a well as full 3D camera. You can download the demo <a href="http://neolbanet.googlecode.com/files/lbanet_1.0_demo.rar">here</a>.</span></p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 12pt; color: #a7fafa;">This new engine will come with a lot of additionnal features to make the game more enjoyable.<br /></span></p>\r\n<p /><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 12pt; color: #a7fafa;" /> \r\n', '\r\n</span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"> </p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p> </p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="color: #a7fafa;"><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;">The new engine is still under development and this is only a demo version (only working in local mode), not the full game. Once completed, it will have the following features (in addition to the existing one):</span></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"> </p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="color: #a7fafa;"><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;">- complete fighting system ( projectile and body contact e.g. saber)</span></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="color: #a7fafa;"><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;"><br /></span></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="color: #a7fafa;"><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;">- new display engine using <a href="http://www.openscenegraph.org">OSG </a>with the following extensions:</span></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify; padding-left: 30px;"><span style="color: #a7fafa;"><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;">- full 3D environment, being able to display any type of map (LBA1 grids, LBA2 outside maps, custom maps)<br /></span></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify; padding-left: 30px;"><span style="color: #a7fafa;"><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;">- real-time lighting system including shadows</span></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify; padding-left: 30px;"><span style="color: #a7fafa;"><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;">- integration with shaders</span></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify; padding-left: 30px;"><span style="color: #a7fafa;"><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;">- can include models (animated or not) from any known design tools (blender, 3dsmax, ...)</span></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify; padding-left: 30px;"><span style="color: #a7fafa;"><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;">- particle system</span></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify; padding-left: 30px;"><span style="color: #a7fafa;"><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;">- fog<br /></span></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify; padding-left: 30px;"><span style="color: #a7fafa;"><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;"><br /></span></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="color: #a7fafa;"><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;">- integration with LUA for extended scripting (NPCs behaviors, custom triggers in game, ...)</span></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"> </p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="color: #a7fafa;"><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;">- 1 server per world giving the world creator more freedom. He will be able to update his world and restart his server at any time whithout interfering with the other worlds.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"> </p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"> </p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="color: #a7fafa;"><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;">The demo includes 3 worlds in order to show the new engine potential:</span></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="color: #a7fafa;"><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;"> - The original lba1 prison map</span></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="color: #a7fafa;"><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;">- A world containing all Lba2 external islands</span></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="color: #a7fafa;"><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;">- A world containing a map made with custom bricks made by mazaka</span></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"> </p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="color: #a7fafa;"><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;">The controls are the same than lbanet, with some additions:</span></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="color: #a7fafa;"><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;">- F10 takes a screenshot</span></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="color: #a7fafa;"><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;">- F11 show the FPS and other stats</span></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="color: #a7fafa;"><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;">- F12 toggle the fullscreen</span></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="color: #a7fafa;"><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;">- Right shift center the camera on twinsen (same as enter key in original LBA2 game)</span></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"> </p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="color: #a7fafa;"><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;">In the option video tab you have a new combobox giving you the choice of camera type. You can play with it and see the different possibilities. Leaving it to auto will let the game decide which camera is the best depedning of the type of map.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"> </p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><span style="color: #a7fafa;"><span style="font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;">Hope you enjoy the demo. Any comments are welcome :)<br /></span></span></p>', 1, 2, 0, 1, '2010-10-10 17:41:36', 66, '', '2010-10-24 19:19:24', 66, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2010-10-10 17:39:12', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', '', 'show_title=\nlink_titles=\nshow_intro=\nshow_section=\nlink_section=\nshow_category=\nlink_category=\nshow_vote=\nshow_author=\nshow_create_date=\nshow_modify_date=\nshow_pdf_icon=\nshow_print_icon=\nshow_email_icon=\nlanguage=\nkeyref=\nreadmore=', 6, 0, 2, '', '', 0, 821, 'robots=\nauthor='),
